quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  41,26,"And those who disbelieve say, \"Do not listen to this Quran and do make a noise in the midst of its reading that you may overcome it"
  41,27,"Therefore, We will certainly make those who disbelieve taste a severe punishment, and We will certainly requite them for the evil deeds they used to do"
  41,28,That is the reward of the enemies of Allah - the Fire. Therein is their eternal home; the payment for denying Our signs
  41,29,"And those who disbelieve will say, \"Our Lord! Show us those who led us astray from among the jinn and men that we may trample them under our feet so that they may be of the lowest"
  41,30,"As for those who say, \"Our Lord is Allah\", then continue steadfast in righteousness, the angels descend upon them, saying, \"Fear not, nor be grieved, and receive good news of the Garden which you were promised"
  41,31,"We are your guardians in the life of this world and in the Hereafter, and you shall have therein what your souls desire and you shall have therein all you ask for"
  41,32,"A provision from the Forgiving, the Merciful"